## Performance Guidelines

### Component Optimization
```typescript
// Use React.memo for components that re-render frequently
const ExpensiveComponent = React.memo(function ExpensiveComponent({ data }) {
  return <div>{/* expensive rendering */}</div>
})

// Use useMemo for expensive calculations
const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => {
  return heavyCalculation(data)
}, [data])

// Use useCallback for event handlers passed to children
const handleClick = useCallback((id: string) => {
  onItemClick(id)
}, [onItemClick])
```

### Database Query Optimization
```typescript
// Use specific selects instead of *
.select('id, title, created_at')

// Use proper indexing
.eq('indexed_column', value)

// Limit results for pagination
.limit(50)

// Order efficiently
.order('created_at', { ascending: false })
```

## Error Handling Patterns

### API Route Error Handling
```typescript
try {
  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from('table_name')
    .insert(insertData)
    
  if (error) throw error
  
  return NextResponse.json({ data })
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Operation failed:', error)
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: 'Internal server error' }, 
    { status: 500 }
  )
}
```

### Component Error Boundaries
```typescript
if (error) {
  return (
    <div className="bg-destructive/10 border border-destructive/20 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p className="text-destructive font-medium">Error: {error}</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Security Considerations

### Authentication Checks
All protected routes and API endpoints must check authentication:
```typescript
const session = await auth()
if (!session?.user?.id) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 })
}

// Role-based access control
const userRole = getUserRole(session.user?.email)
if (userRole !== 'admin' && userRole !== 'teacher') {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Forbidden' }, { status: 403 })
}
```

### Input Validation
```typescript
// Validate required fields
if (!body.title || !body.question) {
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: 'Missing required fields' }, 
    { status: 400 }
  )
}

// Validate data types
if (typeof body.points !== 'number') {
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: 'Points must be a number' }, 
    { status: 400 }
  )
}
```

## Accessibility Requirements

### ARIA Support
- Use proper ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Provide screen reader alternatives for visual content
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements
- Use semantic HTML elements

### Focus Management
```typescript
const buttonRef = useRef<HTMLButtonElement>(null)

useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen) {
    buttonRef.current?.focus()
  }
}, [isOpen])
```

## Git Workflow

### Commit Message Format
```
type(scope): description

feat(assignments): add AI-powered question generation
fix(auth): resolve session persistence issue
docs(readme): update installation instructions
refactor(components): improve type safety in forms
```

### Branch Naming
- `feature/description` - New features
- `fix/description` - Bug fixes  
- `refactor/description` - Code improvements
- `docs/description` - Documentation updates

## Code Review Checklist

Before submitting code:
- [ ] All imports organized correctly
- [ ] TypeScript types are specific and accurate
- [ ] Error handling is implemented
- [ ] Authentication checks are in place (if needed)
- [ ] Tests are written and passing
- [ ] Accessibility considerations addressed
- [ ] Performance optimizations applied
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed